    <section id="aboutTheRules" class="cf">
      <div class="c1"></div>
      <div class="c4">
        <h1 class="light">WebFWD Code of Conduct</h1>
        <p class="serif">WebFWD is a community. We created the program to foster innovation through collaboration - and help accelerate your progress where we can. This means that you are required to play an active role and not just consume. You, your team, the other participants, our mentors, friends, the wider Mozilla crew and the WebFWD team are this community.</p>
        <p class="serif">Our community has a few ground rules. Play nicely by them, become an active participant and enjoy the ride.</p>
        <ol class="serif" style="font-size:16px;">
          <li>Be active. Share, engage, discuss. Our central hub for this is Yammer.</li>
          <li>Be helpful. We all have specific areas of strength, offer help in your area of expertise.</li>
          <li>Be positive. There are enough nay-sayers in the world. Share a positive outlook.</li>
          <li>Be grateful. You get free stuff - as in "no strings attached." Be kind & grateful to the people providing this.</li>
          <li>Be respectful. We don't tolerate bad behavior. We are all in the same boat.</li>
          <li>Take it seriously. We all invest time, resources and money into WebFWD: please honor this.</li>
          <li>Pay it Forward. Give back by serving and doing good to others.</li>
          <li>Help us build. Provide feedback and spread the word about WebFWD.</li>
          <li>Have fun. Without fun, all this other stuff is meaningless.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

